---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Learning";
const description = "How I trained my judgment through sustained study and applied practice.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
<section class="learning-page">
  <header class="learning-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Learning as method</p>
    <h1>Learning</h1>
    <p class="learning-kicker">I follow where the questions get harder.</p>
    <p class="learning-lede">
      Since 1992, I’ve returned to structured learning alongside my work. Not for credentials. For constraint. The goal has been consistent: sharpen how I think when decisions carry consequence.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="learning-timeline" aria-label="Learning timeline">
    <article class="learning-moment">
      <span class="learning-year">1992–1994</span>
      <h2>Oklahoma State University</h2>
      <p>
        Early study established the pattern. I was drawn to environments that forced clarity, even before I knew where it would lead.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="learning-moment">
      <span class="learning-year">2005</span>
      <h2>Stanford University</h2>
      <p>
        I brought my team at Yahoo! into a course focused on improvisation. The objective wasn’t performance. It was collaboration: learning how to build on each other’s thinking, articulate ideas in motion, and design without shutting down possibility.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="learning-moment">
      <span class="learning-year">2016</span>
      <h2>Stanford ICME</h2>
      <p>
        Coursework marked a deliberate turn toward data and systems. I focused on how decisions get made when information is incomplete, and how reasoning breaks under pressure.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="learning-moment">
      <span class="learning-year">2017–today</span>
      <h2>MIT</h2>
      <p>
        Sustained study through MIT programs has focused on design, AI, and decision systems. This work has been self-directed and ongoing, built on repetition rather than milestones.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="learning-proof" aria-label="How learning shows up in the work">
    <div class="proof-card">
      <span>01</span>
      <h2>Separate signal from output</h2>
      <p>I look past what a system returns and ask what the output actually means under real conditions.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="proof-card">
      <span>02</span>
      <h2>Design for interpretation</h2>
      <p>I build for the human layer where uncertainty, escalation, and judgment determine whether a system holds.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="proof-card">
      <span>03</span>
      <h2>Stay accountable when wrong</h2>
      <p>I treat failure as expected, not exceptional, and design systems that can be challenged, corrected, and trusted again.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="learning-close">
    <p>
      I don’t use learning to expand what I know. I use it to reduce how often I’m wrong in systems that matter.
    </p>
    <p>
      Learning is still active. Today it meant explaining equatorial storms and jet streams to my six-year-old.
    </p>
  </section>
</section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .learning-page {
    max-width: 1040px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.25rem 5rem;
  }

  .learning-hero {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .eyebrow,
  .learning-year,
  .proof-card span {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #3e5a82;
  }

  .learning-hero h1 {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1rem;
  }

  .learning-kicker {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .learning-lede {
    font-size: 1.12rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .learning-timeline {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 0 0 3.5rem;
  }

  .learning-moment,
  .proof-card {
    border: 1px solid rgba(62, 90, 130, 0.22);
    background: rgba(248, 247, 244, 0.58);
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .learning-moment h2,
  .proof-card h2 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0.6rem 0 0.65rem;
  }

  .learning-moment p,
  .proof-card p,
  .learning-close p {
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .learning-proof {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .learning-close {
    max-width: 720px;
    border-left: 3px solid #3e5a82;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .learning-close p:first-child {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .learning-timeline,
    .learning-proof {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .learning-page {
      padding-top: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>